==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Metaxylene
<hw>Met`a*xy"lene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>meta-</ets> + <ets>xylene</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>That variety of xylene, or dimethyl benzene, in which the two
methyl groups occupy the meta position with reference to each other. It
is a colorless inflammable liquid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

